Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.14,0:01:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All I was doing\Nis what I was trained to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.06,0:01:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,-That's how I think of it, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.18,0:01:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize\Nhow weak and fragile you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.60,0:01:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This was his first day\Ngoing to that office.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.44,0:01:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-We had his picture posted.\N-He was happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.90,0:01:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I have pulmonary fibrosis…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.44,0:01:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw the building\Ncome down, I just prayed, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.61,0:01:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nif we were just in denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.57,0:01:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-Thought he'd end up in the trash.\N-They're done digging.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.24,0:01:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,-Don't know how it could get easy.\N-Have to come to terms with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.58,0:01:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,-The rest of them, all gone.\N-I lost a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.63,0:01:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You want other information?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.01,0:01:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.26,0:01:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.97,0:01:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm angry with God,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.51,0:01:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm angry with our country, also,\Nbecause they let this happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.90,0:01:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My beautiful boy…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.57,0:01:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,…was burned alive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.11,0:01:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.83,0:02:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't… We don't even have a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.37,0:02:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone took your child…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.46,0:02:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and blew them up…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.47,0:02:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't even have a fingernail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.31,0:02:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you go on from there?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.19,0:02:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you calculate that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.53,0:02:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-What is life worth?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a trick question, people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.12,0:02:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's gonna give us a number? Uh…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.63,0:02:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Back row. Uh, you there, Mr. Barron.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.59,0:03:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Big boy voice here, counselor.\NTell us, where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.34,0:03:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was raised in Wichita.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.30,0:03:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Kansas. Farm boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.76,0:03:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, good, good.\NYou were raised on one, a farm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.64,0:03:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My girlfriend's father owned one.\NHe grew sorghum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.23,0:03:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorghum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.15,0:03:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Girlfriend's father grew sorghum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.11,0:03:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Paula Tano.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.36,0:03:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Paula Tano, you are now\NMr. Barron's girlfriend's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.74,0:03:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't laugh, people, it's very sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.91,0:03:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Barron just died,\Ntragically crushed by a combine harvester
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.66,0:03:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in Miss Paula Tano's sorghum field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.62,0:03:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Dickerson,\Nyou're now representing Mr. Barron.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.63,0:03:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And where's Miss Chen?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.55,0:03:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Chen, you're representing\NAmalgamated Caterpillar,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.13,0:03:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,manufacturer of said combine harvester,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.35,0:03:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which took poor young Mr. Barron's life,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.26,0:03:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Kansas state civil action
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.43,0:03:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of Mr. Barron v. Mr. Barron's\Ngirlfriend's father's sorghum farm
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.73,0:03:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Caterpillar company.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.23,0:04:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Miss Chen, how much do you offer\NMr. Dickerson to settle this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.95,0:04:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let me rephrase.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.16,0:04:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How much is Mr. Barron's life worth?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.87,0:04:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Give us a number.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.50,0:04:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Two million?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.17,0:04:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I'm in law school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.17,0:04:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I could be earning that before I'm 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.30,0:04:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you aced the final, maybe,\Nand if you weren't dead, but you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is now Mr. Dickerson's decision,\Nalong with Mr… Your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.35,0:04:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,-Patel.\N-Patel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.69,0:04:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Patel is the poor bereaved mother\Nof Mr. Barron.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.78,0:04:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Three million?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.40,0:04:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Two-point-seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.91,0:04:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There you have it. There's the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.28,0:04:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,To be clear, you haven't stumbled\Ninto a philosophy course.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.00,0:04:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the law is concerned,\Nthis question actually has an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:04:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer is a number,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.88,0:05:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.81,0:05:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Yes, 55 per victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.19,0:05:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and both sides agreed to walk.\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.61,0:05:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No one thinks it's fair,\Nbut fair is not the goal here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.03,0:05:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finish and move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.99,0:05:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Well, thank you, Senator.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.54,0:05:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Feinberg, you have a message\Nfrom Judge Clinton.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.04,0:05:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Vic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just remember me when POTUS calls\Nabout a vacancy on the Supreme Court.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.79,0:05:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw Rehnquist the other day.\NHe's looking pale.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.80,0:05:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I said he's looking pale.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.68,0:05:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He-- Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.59,0:05:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I lost him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.55,0:05:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-Probably a good thing.\N-It was a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.64,0:05:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually the funny ones,\Nyou don't have to announce that after.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.35,0:05:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I just saved the taxpayers\Na year's worth of courtroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.98,0:05:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think he really hung up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.48,0:06:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he's off\Ncommissioning a monument.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.31,0:06:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,-I have a forum to run.\N-No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.27,0:06:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Darryl Barnes, Esq.\NI have an important question for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.28,0:06:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-Is this birthday cake?\N-Margo in Accounting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.57,0:06:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.74,0:06:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-Is that the important question?\N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.99,0:06:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she save any for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.70,0:06:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Gloria, where are we on that email?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"And so I would ask…"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.96,0:06:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I would insist…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.04,0:06:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Not "ask," "insist."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.96,0:06:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,…that you be on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.84,0:06:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a very busy schedule that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.34,0:06:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so punctuality will be imperative.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.05,0:06:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Please promptly advise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.93,0:06:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"Love, Dad"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.48,0:06:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yeah, yeah. Love, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.27,0:06:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,-Okay. I'll type this up right now.\N-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.67,0:07:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Remind me why we're building this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.30,0:07:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of buying that cute little place\Non Cape Charles?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.01,0:07:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-Fog.\N-You could still commute.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.18,0:07:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The numbers show Cape Charles\Nis more than twice as likely
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.89,0:07:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to be fogged in on any given day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.47,0:07:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-That's not a real statistic.\N-Two-point-two is the statistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.94,0:07:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wanna retire to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.31,0:07:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have heard that people that base\Ntheir future happiness on weather data
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.44,0:07:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,-are 100% less likely to be fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he only just looks at me?\NDo you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.11,0:07:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not retiring anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.71,0:08:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Kenny.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.57,0:08:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they want to put in\Nanother shoe store.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.78,0:09:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We need another one of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.33,0:09:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They wanna take out\Nthose beautiful arched windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.96,0:09:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the ones that have\Nthe Corinthian carved cartouche-y things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.21,0:09:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They wanna take them out\Nand put in modern ones
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.09,0:09:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so they can hawk more sneakers. It's just…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.76,0:09:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Not on your watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.17,0:09:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No. Now you're mocking me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.43,0:09:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There's chicken piccata\Nin the fridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.89,0:09:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to post this. Just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.56,0:09:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Power to the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.77,0:09:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.96,0:09:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you can take it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:09:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,-Who's that?\N-You can take it apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.05,0:09:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey, love.\N-Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.76,0:09:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can snap that back in,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.17,0:10:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,take it apart and…\NA shorter wing span. Just putting--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.34,0:10:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, come eat, please.\NBreakfast is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.97,0:10:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-Quickly.\N-Yay, breakfast!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.10,0:10:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,-Thank you.\N-Owen, slow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.89,0:10:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.31,0:10:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta go. Love ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.52,0:10:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's, uh,\Nexactly the one that I got.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.40,0:10:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-What are we doing after school?\N-All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.86,0:10:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.72,0:10:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.64,0:10:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-Right now, I don't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.85,0:10:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.24,0:11:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,…freaking out, hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.78,0:11:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.58,0:11:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, how you doing?\NWhat's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.29,0:11:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-Excuse me, sir, is there any--\N-Can't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.13,0:11:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-What's happening?\N-Did you find her somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.97,0:11:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn on the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.19,0:11:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.44,0:11:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The shock from the attacks\Nin New York and D.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.49,0:11:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-reverberate across the entire nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.99,0:11:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Our correspondent,\NTanya Riddle, has been told
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that state officials are working\Nto strengthen security all across…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.45,0:11:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Officials\Nat Somerset County Airport
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.41,0:11:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,confirm the crash of a large plane\Nnorth of that airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.58,0:11:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The army has been placed\Nat Prescott, Delta.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Firefighters\Nand police officers
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.88,0:11:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are frantically trying to help
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.51,0:12:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,those people who have been hurt,\Nwho perhaps have not been rescued.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.63,0:12:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,With tragedy so great,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.39,0:12:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,tonight, a city comes together\Nsearching for safety and comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.68,0:12:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,…of a hundred waiting\Nfor their turn
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.18,0:12:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to go into the World Trade Center area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.52,0:12:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,…the days to come,\Nto the rescue those who may be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.94,0:12:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have, at this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.36,0:12:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,well over a thousand people\Nconfirmed dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.86,0:12:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The 300 that are missing\Nthat he talked about,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.82,0:12:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the 800 at the Pentagon,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.53,0:12:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,266 who were on those airplanes today,\Npassengers and crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.29,0:12:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, we're now up to about 1300,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.33,0:12:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is expected to go much higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.50,0:12:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty-four hundred people altogether\Nwere killed in Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.13,0:12:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They were military personnel\Nfor the most part.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.09,0:12:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a military attack\Non military installations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.84,0:12:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We know who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.84,0:12:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a different kind of a war\Nin a new century.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.74,0:13:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,…that involves so many people?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.08,0:13:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think all of that\Nis going to have to be sifted out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.54,0:13:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that in the midst\Nof our outrage and anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.17,0:13:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, President Bush is right,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.51,0:13:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to show the world\Nhow we respond to this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.51,0:13:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, both with determination, uh…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.64,0:13:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-So, what did you tell Kennedy?\N-That I'd think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.31,0:13:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That you're my partner,\Nand I'd have to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.39,0:13:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hah. Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.15,0:13:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I know why he asked us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.65,0:13:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We're one of five or six firms\Nwith this kind of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.03,0:13:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If that. If that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.44,0:13:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah. Asbestos, Agent Orange.\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.70,0:13:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were hot-button cases too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.82,0:13:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'll let you know\Nhow the committee hearing goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.83,0:13:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.18,0:14:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.14,0:14:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-I know Teddy appreciates it.\N-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.35,0:14:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We want our best trial lawyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.77,0:14:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be needing your support\Non this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.86,0:14:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah.\N-Your people okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.61,0:14:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,-Kids, family?\N-Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.15,0:14:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Mike was at his dorm at NYU.\NHe's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.82,0:14:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He was shaken up, but, uh… What thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.08,0:14:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A new bill on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.62,0:14:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The Air Transportation\NSafety and System Stabilization Act.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.42,0:14:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-Wait, they're bailing out the airlines?\N-More like the whole economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.63,0:14:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If the victims of these attacks\Nor their families
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.42,0:14:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,attempt to sue the airline industry\Nfor damages, we will go bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.14,0:14:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And never mind whether they win or not,\Nthe legal costs alone…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.06,0:14:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when we might as well\Njust hand those terrorists the victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.14,0:15:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're paralyzed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.52,0:15:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Deliveries, commuter travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.81,0:15:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole economy grinding to a halt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.86,0:15:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're facing is a national emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.94,0:15:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,-Mm-hmm.\N-Lee?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.28,0:15:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.32,0:15:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-Help us come up with another way.\N-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.66,0:15:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, brass tacks here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.08,0:15:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're trying to prevent\Nlawsuits from the victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.04,0:15:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-That's what they're saying.\N-That's not what we're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.42,0:15:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called due process.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.79,0:15:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Limit. We're saying limit civil suits\Nagainst the airlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.96,0:15:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Denying recourse to the people\Nmost impacted by these attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.30,0:15:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop grandstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.30,0:15:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're proposing\Nis a treasury fund
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.51,0:15:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,offering tort-style compensation\Nto the victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.60,0:15:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,For their economic losses,\Nsomething for pain and suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.48,0:15:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but coming from us, Congress,\Nnot the courts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.23,0:15:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And in exchange,\Nthe claimants promise not to sue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.86,0:15:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-Corporate bailout.\N-Chrissakes, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.98,0:15:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-What, you're calling it charity?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.11,0:15:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Government-sponsored charity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.70,0:15:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,With strings attached?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.66,0:15:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken, help me out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.87,0:16:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A lawsuit could take decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.79,0:16:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.37,0:16:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,After it crashes the economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.17,0:16:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the victims might still lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.04,0:16:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is for their own good,\Nand the nation's.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.68,0:16:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. How many, uh…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.85,0:16:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How many victims are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.18,0:16:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we don't really know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.19,0:16:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A special master we select\Nwill have to negotiate all settlements.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.11,0:16:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A flat fee would\Nbe another option.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.94,0:16:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The same dollar value\Nfor every loss of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.24,0:16:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But those towers had CEOs and janitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.33,0:16:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't all say yes to the same number.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.91,0:16:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if they did,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.29,0:16:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody wanna go on record\Nwith what that number is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.00,0:16:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, pretty soon somebody's\Ngonna have to do the vulgar work
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.92,0:16:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of putting numbers on a check.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.60,0:17:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're saying, what,\Nyou wanna do this job?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.10,0:17:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no, I mean…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.52,0:17:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I mean,\Nwe're discussing it right now, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.15,0:17:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you're telling me\Nyou're not sick about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.32,0:17:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,watching all this on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.37,0:17:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,-Of course I'm sick about it.\N-Well…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's just tough stuff, Kenny.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.17,0:17:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, I know. It is very tough, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.46,0:17:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're not exactly…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.01,0:17:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.34,0:17:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not a rabbi or a priest,\Nyou're a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.55,0:17:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. And that's exactly\Nwhat these people need right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.01,0:17:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a process here, you know.\NI hire a team,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.14,0:17:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I draft an objective formula,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.14,0:17:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and I dispense reasonable payments.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.61,0:17:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.65,0:17:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's no different\Nthan my previous cases in that regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.23,0:17:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, this is something I'm good at.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.61,0:17:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.78,0:18:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something I can do to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.17,0:18:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Judge Weinstein told me\Nhow you reached a settlement on DES.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.89,0:18:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten years of courthouse war.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.43,0:18:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You brought both sides to a motel room,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.47,0:18:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,told them they could stay\Nas long as they wanted,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.43,0:18:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but they couldn't leave\Nuntil they reached a settlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.14,0:18:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-Is that really true?\N-It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.98,0:18:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,-I did let them order room service.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.69,0:18:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Attorney General, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.28,0:18:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,People are rational animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.78,0:18:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I find if you…\Nif you force them to the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.45,0:18:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,most behave in a way\Nthat makes the most sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.20,0:18:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe\Nyou live in Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.45,0:18:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in politics, uh, conflict sells.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.96,0:18:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I find that what works best is compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.79,0:18:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No one walks away too happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.21,0:18:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,just happy enough to walk away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.80,0:19:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you walk away today,\Nwhat outcome makes you happy enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.05,0:19:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to have the job, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.97,0:19:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No one wants this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.39,0:19:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that narrows down\Nyour options.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.23,0:19:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.53,0:19:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that you're a Democrat,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.61,0:19:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Teddy's former chief of staff.\NDid you hope I'd overlook that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.91,0:19:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was hoping\Nyou could see that as a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.91,0:19:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you said yourself,\Nthis is a hot potato.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.45,0:19:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know if you give it to an insider,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.87,0:19:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, a party man\Nor friend of the president, then…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.25,0:19:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-They'll blame us if it fails.\N-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.13,0:19:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick me, it's the opposition's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.38,0:19:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless for some reason, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.68,0:19:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,by some miracle, I pull this off,\Nin which case…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.18,0:19:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't we look open-minded,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.60,0:19:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,reaching all the way\Nacross the aisle to find you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.14,0:19:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It is felt, and I'm speaking\Nfor the White House here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.94,0:19:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that for the program\Nto succeed in staving off
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.90,0:20:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a full-on economic cataclysm,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.41,0:20:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,no fewer than 80%\Nof eligible claimants must opt in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.58,0:20:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That means voluntarily choose not to sue.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.71,0:20:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, that shouldn't be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.46,0:20:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, congratulations, Special Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.84,0:20:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-You got any more surprises for me?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.22,0:20:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to work for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.09,0:20:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, hey, everyone come in here for just a…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.72,0:20:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Camille and I want to thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.81,0:20:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for shouldering the firm's\Nday-to-day responsibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.61,0:20:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,while we devote our time to this pro bono.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.98,0:20:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, it's not gonna be easy,\Nand we sure welcome all of your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.99,0:20:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we do our job\Nthe way I know we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.74,0:20:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,well, we just might make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So thank you. And, uh… Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.88,0:21:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.59,0:21:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is you psyching yourself up,\Nor considering a quick escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.43,0:21:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When's the last time\NI took on something I couldn't handle?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.94,0:21:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,-Well, Brockton track meet, 1961.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.40,0:21:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I came in second.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.48,0:21:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And you still remember who beat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.44,0:21:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Phil Leonardo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.53,0:21:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was robbed, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.57,0:21:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know how to lose, Kenny.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.45,0:21:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, this one's, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.25,0:21:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,not that kind of case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.71,0:21:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.25,0:21:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.58,0:21:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken. Call for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.88,0:21:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.22,0:21:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna take it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah.\N-Line one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.22,0:21:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this is Ken Feinberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.18,0:21:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Please hold for the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.06,0:21:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-Well… Hello, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.31,0:22:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-Ken? Is this Ken Feinberg?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.40,0:22:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken, I wanna\Ncongratulate you on this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.65,0:22:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah. Yeah, Ashcroft was impressed.\N-Well--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.90,0:22:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, you're taking\Nthe heat on this, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.70,0:22:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I would not wish this job\Non my worst enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.83,0:22:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They tell me you're type of guy\Nthat takes no prisoners.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.12,0:22:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,-Well--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.83,0:22:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm kidding you, counselor.\NI like to josh.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.29,0:22:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-Did I scare you off?\N-No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.71,0:22:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, sir. I'm still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.29,0:22:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there you are. Okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.00,0:22:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you, Mr. President.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.09,0:22:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And, look, you won't regret this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.59,0:22:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure hope not.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.51,0:22:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.26,0:23:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-Morning.\N-Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.51,0:23:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I assume you've all met,\Nbut this is Priya Khundi.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.27,0:24:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Priya graduated first\Nin my class last year, Georgetown.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.19,0:24:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And after she passed the bar,\NI offered her a place here,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.98,0:24:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but she, very politely, turned me down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.90,0:24:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for a big, fancy company\Ndown on Wall Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.61,0:24:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Their main office\Nwas on the 98th floor of the North Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.03,0:24:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,-Ah.\N-So we're very lucky to have her.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.16,0:24:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you all have copies of the statute?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.00,0:24:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,H.R.2926,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.00,0:24:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the Airline Transportation\NSafety and System Stabilization Act.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.71,0:24:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, who's read it? Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.22,0:24:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-Did it take you long?\N-Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.05,0:24:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-You wanna know why?\N-Because it's short?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.34,0:24:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, yeah, that\Nand there's no law in this law.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.27,0:24:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What it says is the victims\Nand their families will be compensated
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.81,0:24:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,based on economic value lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.86,0:24:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What that means,\Nthey left up to the special master. Us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.11,0:24:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to us to write the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.32,0:24:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken and I have done it in other cases
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.28,0:24:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is always messy,\Nso get ready for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.53,0:25:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, who's eligible?\NWho gets how much? Where we draw the line?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.62,0:25:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do we start?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.63,0:25:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Eighty percent, Priya.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.38,0:25:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our target from the DOJ.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.13,0:25:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't hit that number,\Nthe plan won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.42,0:25:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Any fewer claimants come aboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.13,0:25:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the lawsuits that result\Ncould crater the economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.26,0:25:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-So we're told.\N-No pressure, people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.89,0:25:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For every claimant,\Nwe'll need to calculate a dollar value
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.73,0:25:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the human loss,\Nwhether it's loss of limb or loss of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.06,0:25:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the people who died that day\Nwere providers for their families.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.03,0:25:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't bring them back,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.44,0:25:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can help their loved ones\Npay their bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.99,0:25:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you people understand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.37,0:25:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not gonna be able to haggle\Nevery case subjectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.33,0:25:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where the math comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.45,0:25:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're, uh, we're gonna need a rubric.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.83,0:25:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the latest\Nactuarial tables
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.75,0:25:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,from the top casualty\Nin life insurance companies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.67,0:25:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll use these numbers as a basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.34,0:25:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you guys study up on these
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.38,0:25:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and help Camille come up with a proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.64,0:26:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so West Street, South Ferry,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.89,0:26:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower Broadway,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.19,0:26:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and Canal Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.06,0:26:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, here's one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.11,0:26:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What if there are multiple dependents?\NHow do we decide who gets the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.32,0:26:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Where there's a will, we follow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.03,0:26:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,-And where there isn't one?\N-We follow the state law.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.70,0:26:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The state they died in,\Nor the state they came from?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.12,0:26:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-The state of residence.\N-What about domestic partners?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.29,0:26:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.08,0:26:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about the deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.29,0:26:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The statute gives us two years\Nand a month from today.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.50,0:26:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's December 22nd, 2003.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.72,0:26:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That feels short.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.09,0:26:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,-Well, not for families in grief.\N-We could file for an extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.43,0:26:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah-ah-ah. Don't you dare. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.85,0:26:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If we extend it, they'll hem\Nand they'll haw, and they won't act.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.85,0:26:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Deadline is our friend here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.15,0:26:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what are we forgetting?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.19,0:26:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.53,0:27:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, we have a dozen lists,\Nbut nothing comprehensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.66,0:27:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The flight manifests and the Pentagon,\Nthose are the easy ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.29,0:27:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,NYPD and FDNY, they have lists.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.54,0:27:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The big companies like Cantor Fitzgerald,\Nthey're putting some lists together,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.21,0:27:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but as for the records\Nof who passed through the doors that day…
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.05,0:27:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.21,0:27:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't even know\Nhow many names we're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.60,0:30:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax.\NWe've done this kind of thing before.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.23,0:30:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, this one is raw.\NThose aren't lawyers out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.77,0:30:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, I can't stand lawyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.23,0:30:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you, running for office?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.36,0:30:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, be a person, not a politician.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.69,0:30:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.78,0:30:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.11,0:30:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-Okay. Good luck.\N-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.80,0:30:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.55,0:30:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.09,0:30:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, as you may know,\NI am Kenneth Feinberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.68,0:30:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the special master
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.97,0:31:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the September 11th\NVictim Compensation Fund.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.60,0:31:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I would like today to tell you--
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.07,0:31:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I'd… I'd like to tell you\Nhow the 9/11 fund will work.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.83,0:31:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You've all been given copies of this,\Nthe presumptive claims formula.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.20,0:31:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.12,0:31:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, and quite soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.33,0:31:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll be sending this along to Congress\Nfor a comment period.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.50,0:31:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.42,0:31:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon approval,\Nthere will be no further changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.55,0:31:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,-Mr. Feinberg?\N-I got a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.59,0:31:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm sorry.\N-I got a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.26,0:31:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could hold your questions\Ntill after my remarks.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.81,0:31:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd ask you to refer to the table\Nat the top of page two.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.36,0:31:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you can see, the formula\Nis actually fairly streamlined.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.19,0:31:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we need one?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.45,0:31:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,-Please just hold your question.\N-Why do we need a formula?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.45,0:31:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.66,0:31:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why isn't it equal payment\Nfor everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.74,0:31:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.91,0:32:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter's life was worth just as much\Nas anybody in a corner office.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.00,0:32:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, that aspect of the law\Nhas been out of our control.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.13,0:32:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My boy was a firefighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.92,0:32:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he… Was he worth less
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.93,0:32:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,than the… than the guy pushing pencils\Nand trading stock?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.89,0:32:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.43,0:32:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly not… not as a human being, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.94,0:32:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Their… Their lives ended the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.94,0:32:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But their mortgages did differ.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.90,0:32:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.11,0:32:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just trying to shut us up\Nso we don't sue.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.74,0:32:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hi.\N-Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.99,0:32:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-Have they… Has it started already?\N-They're just starting.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.87,0:32:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-Good, okay.\N-Would you like a claims form?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.16,0:32:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, no, I have my own.\NI printed it off the web.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.08,0:32:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a typo on page three\Nthat you should know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.25,0:32:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,-And also, there are…\N-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.59,0:32:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-I should sign in here, right?\N-Yes, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.17,0:32:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There… And there are more issues\Nthat need to be addressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.97,0:32:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They're substantive, okay.\NAnd they need to be addressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.55,0:32:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.77,0:33:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean…\NLook, as a legal professional,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.56,0:33:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I know chasing a lawsuit is a big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.23,0:33:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-Did you lose anybody?\N-Look--
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.07,0:33:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-Did you lose anybody in your family?\N-I just… Let me explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.40,0:33:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Congress mandated\Nthat I calculate the economic value.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.24,0:33:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-Economical.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.29,0:33:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.50,0:33:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just afraid of being sued.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.33,0:33:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-I understand how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.17,0:33:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,-Understand?\N-Look, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.75,0:33:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,-What I mean is, I sympathize.\N-Who did you lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.80,0:33:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, as a legal professional,\NI will tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.09,0:33:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be years in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.05,0:33:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You might win, you might not.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.64,0:33:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is fast money and it's tax-free.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.60,0:33:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your thinking caps on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.23,0:33:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the only game in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.23,0:33:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-How dare you!\N-You think this is a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.06,0:33:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm sorry.\N-This isn't a game!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.94,0:33:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-What do you know about law?\N-Who do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.82,0:33:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We lost brothers.\NNow they sent some Jew lawyer…
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.20,0:34:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish… I wish we could spit on your grave\Nthe way you spit on ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.79,0:34:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,-Please.\N-Wait, everyone. Wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.04,0:34:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This man, he did not cause our situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.29,0:34:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here to tell us how the government\Nintends to deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.30,0:34:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And I for one\Nwould just like to hear him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.80,0:34:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.72,0:34:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.55,0:34:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. And I… I was…
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.18,0:34:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, look, as I was…
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.56,0:34:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This meeting is only…
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.65,0:34:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's purely introductory, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.82,0:34:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Any questions you have\Nthat aren't answered in the pamphlet,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.45,0:34:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I will make my staff available\Nfor private hearings
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.82,0:34:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,every business day\Nbetween now and the filing deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.84,0:34:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.00,0:34:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe a poor choice of words\Nhere and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.34,0:34:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Here and there?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.38,0:35:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-Camille?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.84,0:35:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-We need to get back to the office.\N-Mr. Feinberg?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.81,0:35:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,-Mr. Feinberg, give me a minute, please?\N-Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.14,0:35:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Frank Donato. I'm sorry to bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.35,0:35:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not at all. Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.81,0:35:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Ken Feinberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.98,0:35:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened there? Did you break that?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.90,0:35:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My son, Andy, broke his last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.69,0:35:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Rugby injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.74,0:35:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,South Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.24,0:35:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm just curious\Nabout this number.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.33,0:35:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.28,0:35:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez. Thank you for… for your courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.54,0:35:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother, too, Nick. Nicholas.\NSame line of company.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.54,0:35:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. Is he here?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.26,0:35:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well…
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.05,0:35:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Gosh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.63,0:35:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I, uh, I lost track of him\Nafter the first one fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.22,0:35:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the captain says\Nhe went back in to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.39,0:35:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that…
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.06,0:35:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That takes a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.52,0:35:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Except there wasn't any use.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.23,0:35:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the engineers, they knew\Nthe second one was coming down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.78,0:36:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They told PD to call out evacs,\Nbut our radios, they're garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.32,0:36:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They hardly work in high-rise buildings,\Nif you believe that, in New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.58,0:36:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, we've been filing\Nthe same damn reports for years,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.45,0:36:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can guess\Nwhere they tell us to shove 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.83,0:36:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why things went so sideways\Nlike they did, negligence,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.75,0:36:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,top-down, cheap, fucking…
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.84,0:36:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-Sorry.\N-It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.80,0:36:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When you file your report, whatever it is\Nthat you do at the end of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.97,0:36:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I want Nicky's story in it,\Nto make sure they change things,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.93,0:36:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it don't ever happen\Nthis way again. Can you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.81,0:36:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-Well--\N-Can you promise me?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.64,0:36:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-We can certainly look into--\N-Not just talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.06,0:36:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I want it to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.90,0:36:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.28,0:36:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-Why I'm still here.\N-I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.24,0:36:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-Believe that.\N-Can you hold? Camille.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.24,0:36:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you come over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.20,0:36:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-Frank, this is Camille Biros.\N-Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.20,0:36:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She's my deputy administrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.83,0:36:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you talk to her,\Nshe can explain the whole process.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.79,0:36:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't need to hear anything else.\NI just…
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.13,0:37:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to give me your word\Non this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.17,0:37:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.76,0:37:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then me and my wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.26,0:37:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nicky's widow, our whole family,\Nwe'll sign up for your fund, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.14,0:37:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Well, we're certainly\Ngoing to take a look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.90,0:37:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Website at the bottom.\NFirst meeting tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.53,0:37:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go, folks.\NFirst meeting tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.65,0:37:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah.\N-First meeting. Would you like one?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.53,0:37:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.\NFirst meeting is tomorrow, if you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.12,0:37:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So Fix The Fund. Here you are.\NTake a few of these, hand them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.71,0:37:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to talk about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.33,0:37:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, not now though.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.09,0:37:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Website on the bottom, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.17,0:37:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hello.\N-Oh, hi. How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.96,0:37:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I wanna thank you\Nfor your help back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.68,0:37:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh.\N-I gotta tell you, I was…
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.13,0:37:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are. Website at the bottom.\NFirst meeting is tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.89,0:37:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,…a little worried when you stood up.\NI'm glad you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.56,0:37:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, I believe in civility,\NMr. Feinberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.52,0:37:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah.\N-Charles Wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.02,0:37:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll be seeing a lot of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.98,0:38:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good to know. And it's Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.61,0:38:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you'll find\Nthat I'm one of your harshest critics.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.07,0:38:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.78,0:38:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my wife died that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.99,0:38:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything about this formula\Noffends me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.57,0:38:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.66,0:38:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go. Take one of those.\NAnd I'll give you one too.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.62,0:38:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I've set up a page on the World Wide Web.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.79,0:38:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Website's there at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.21,0:38:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called Fix The Fund.\NAnd here you go. Fix The Fund.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.50,0:38:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go. There's two there.\NAnd, um, if you'd like to visit it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.05,0:38:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and come to our meeting,\Nwe have the first meeting, uh, tomorrow…
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.93,0:38:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go. Take that please.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.26,0:38:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd… I'd love it if you would attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.35,0:38:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, I have this for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.76,0:38:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something…\NAnd there are a number of notes
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.77,0:38:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and corrections and things.\NIt's important you address those.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.81,0:38:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are. Take these, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.52,0:38:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at the website on the bottom.\NThere's a couple of them there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.07,0:38:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-Nice to meet you.\N-All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.82,0:38:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Fix The Fund.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.45,0:38:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,-We're not gonna rewrite the formula.\N-They don't trust us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.37,0:38:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't understand\Nthis is for their own good.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.37,0:38:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The airlines would bury them in litigation\Nuntil they had nothing left.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.66,0:38:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I don't know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.87,0:39:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is different.\NDidn't you feel it in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.88,0:39:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our other cases like this,\NAgent Orange, Asbestos,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.21,0:39:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,those were settled after years in court.\NPeople had moved on.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.84,0:39:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,These people aren't there yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.47,0:39:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Camille, they're emotional right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.72,0:39:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to be objective toward them.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.26,0:39:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey, that's for you, Feinberg!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.81,0:39:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck you!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.77,0:39:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What the…
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.24,0:40:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Families got in last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.87,0:40:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Cleary Gottlieb helped us out\Nwith the immigration status and the INS,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.62,0:40:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so we'll use their conference room.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.80,0:40:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.14,0:40:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, it's just, you know,\Nsmall spaces these days, and heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.60,0:40:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine. It's…
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.15,0:40:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you've been informed,\Nbut I wanna reassure you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.32,0:40:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that your citizenship\Nor your immigration status
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.78,0:41:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,will have absolutely no effect\Non our process here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.16,0:41:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything you tell us\Nwill be kept strictly confidential.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.45,0:41:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all looking at your tables\Nand not liking what we're seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.53,0:41:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only factoring in\Nyearly compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.12,0:41:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What about commissions, bonuses?\NWe represent high-worth individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.33,0:41:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of income comes and goes.\NThere's no guarantees with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.50,0:41:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,-That's why we stick to the salaries.\N-That's unacceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.42,0:41:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll also have to strike this rule\Ndeducting life insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.09,0:41:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not a negotiation here--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.67,0:41:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should our clients' families\Nbe penalized for planning well?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.51,0:41:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.26,0:42:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,-No one's being penalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.26,0:42:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.43,0:42:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just being paid off\Nto keep our clients out of court.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.31,0:42:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an oversimplification.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.44,0:42:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the purpose of the fund, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.65,0:42:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the room, too, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.73,0:42:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I do wanna point out that the law requires
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.53,0:42:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we base awards on income,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.24,0:42:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but we've decided on a floor payout
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.45,0:42:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for all lost lives of $200,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.73,0:42:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, mind you, that's just a minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.77,0:42:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that split between more people,\Nor just the families here?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.15,0:42:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, no, it's not a split at all.\NIt's per decedent.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.67,0:43:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a report by an economist,\Na distinguished one,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.71,0:43:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,predicting future compensation\Ngrowth rates for our clients.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.22,0:43:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We suggest you use\Nthose numbers as a baseline.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.39,0:43:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We're here as friends, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.55,0:43:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Your formula may be enough\Nfor waitresses at Windows on the World,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.06,0:43:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but our clients expect a little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.60,0:43:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they can't get it from the fund,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.94,0:43:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll seek that remuneration elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.49,0:43:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.41,0:43:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Pack of wolves out for blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.87,0:43:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.83,0:43:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.55,0:44:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-Are they all here to meet with the staff?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.97,0:44:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Priya and the others are helping out.\NI'm meeting with as many as I can myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.72,0:44:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh good, good. Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.47,0:44:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Most would rather meet with you, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.68,0:44:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They lost loved ones\Nthat are gone forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.02,0:44:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing you do will fill that hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.23,0:44:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll feel cold and cruel at times
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.19,0:44:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can't make them happy, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.91,0:44:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,…that's the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.66,0:44:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So just try to remember\Nwhy you're doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.17,0:44:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I… I hope this is all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.63,0:44:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The stenographer will be here\Njust to keep a record of our conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.89,0:44:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.01,0:44:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Is… Why don't you, um…
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.64,0:44:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you tell me\Nabout your loved one,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.94,0:44:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ann-Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.52,0:44:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Page 14, um, Part 2K
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.53,0:45:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,talks about supporting documents\NI should enclose,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.15,0:45:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,like financial stuff, so I…
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.61,0:45:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I dug up\Nall his files here,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.12,0:45:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what I could find.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.41,0:45:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I don't know where to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.96,0:45:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if we can make sense of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.25,0:45:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It asks here if she was suffering\Nfrom any medical disabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.38,0:45:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean? If she was,\Nyou gonna cut the amount of money?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.51,0:45:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,-Well, not necessarily.\N-Bullshit you guys are pulling.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.18,0:45:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is like going\Nto an insurance company.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.10,0:45:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta watch your back\Nwith every thing you say with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.43,0:45:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the same thing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.15,0:45:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My kids need money for the both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.36,0:45:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't have anybody left.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.28,0:45:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way to cut me a check\Nbefore the official deadline?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.49,0:45:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That morning,\Nshe was scheduled for a different flight,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.83,0:45:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but another girl called in sick,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.17,0:45:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and so, it was my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.67,0:46:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh…
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.13,0:46:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's the one\Nwho called the tower on the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.39,0:46:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Air Traffic Control,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.05,0:46:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,they played it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.10,0:46:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She must have been so scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.56,0:46:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,She sounded so calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.90,0:46:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So the elevators came,\Nand everybody piled on,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.24,0:46:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but there wasn't enough room,\Nand so Greg said,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.66,0:46:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's okay, everyone. You go ahead."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.04,0:46:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There were two women who weren't ready,\Nand so he said, "I'll wait with them."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.84,0:46:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And so everyone else got out,\Nand another elevator never came.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.60,0:46:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know that part of the story
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.97,0:46:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because he called me\Nwhen they were trapped there
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.56,0:46:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to say that he loved me
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.60,0:47:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.77,0:47:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He said…
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.53,0:47:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me that he was trapped,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.70,0:47:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was having difficulty breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.91,0:47:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I could hear the women\Nscreaming in the background
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.25,0:47:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that they didn't wanna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.00,0:47:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And just then he heard\Nan announcement. They were…
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.30,0:47:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.34,0:47:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They were announcing on the loudspeakers,\N"Please evacuate the building."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.35,0:47:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And Greg was…
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.81,0:47:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He always had a sense of humor. And he…
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.98,0:47:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,While he was talking to me,\Nhe actually started to laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.65,0:47:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He was joking to me saying that,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.90,0:47:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"I think I know\NI have to get out of the building."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.49,0:47:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was laughing so hard,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.57,0:47:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,until he said, "I have to go now
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.04,0:48:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because I can't talk anymore,\Nbecause I'm having trouble with air."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.78,0:48:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I know\NI'm not officially his next of kin.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.95,0:48:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We never made it to Vermont.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.99,0:48:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And Tom's parents don't, uh…
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.46,0:48:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they're a pretty traditional\Nmilitary family.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.00,0:48:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They pretend I don't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.72,0:48:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm the one he called,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.51,0:48:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,before the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.05,0:48:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,not them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.81,0:49:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Machine picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.81,0:49:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't home.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.53,0:49:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm so sorry.\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.11,0:49:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I know the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.91,0:49:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,State law says\Nwe were nothing to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.91,0:49:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'd like you to hear his voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.46,0:49:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hi, hon.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.00,0:49:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,By now I guess you've heard\Nabout the mess in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.01,0:49:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Um…
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.67,0:49:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a plane just hit here, too,\Non the western side of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.26,0:49:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-It went right through the E and D rings.\N-Okay, that's…
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.93,0:49:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you turn that off?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.14,0:49:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nif they're showing it on the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.35,0:49:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.89,0:49:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.10,0:49:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough. I don't wanna listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.48,0:49:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a civilian contractor\Nat the Pentagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.28,0:49:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They were gonna have a civil union,\Nbut Tom's parents…
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.82,0:50:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-They won't even take Graham's calls.\N-And what did you tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.95,0:50:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him that Virginia state law\Nhas no protection for same-sex couples,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.37,0:50:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and our rules are tied to state law.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.88,0:50:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's it then.\NI mean, our hands are tied.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.26,0:50:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-We can't insert ourselves in--\N-Why can't we make exceptions?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.72,0:50:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There are others.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.09,0:50:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Last week, a widow came in with cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.14,0:50:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She needs more than we can give her\Nby the rules, and she needs it expedited.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.06,0:50:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't cherry pick one case over another.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.90,0:50:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't write new rules\Nfor every claimant.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.90,0:50:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,-I know this is personal to you--
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.73,0:50:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't in those rooms, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.11,0:50:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,-You didn't listen to them.\N-We're not therapists.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.74,0:50:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I right? It's not our job.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.66,0:50:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I…
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.08,0:50:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like I don't care.\NOf course I care.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.54,0:50:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you not care?\NThat's why we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.84,0:50:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But I need to stay impartial\Nfor this to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.21,0:50:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We set rules for a reason.\NWe set deadlines for a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.84,0:51:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.64,0:51:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Camille, go on, tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.60,0:51:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Priya.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.94,0:51:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.28,0:51:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey.\N-You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.15,0:51:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just…
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.65,0:51:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks\NI'm taking it too personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.82,0:51:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, that is out of line.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.12,0:51:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.70,0:51:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he's right, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.21,0:51:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is personal for me. I…
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.92,0:51:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can't be objective,\Nthen maybe I shouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.84,0:51:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I just…\NI think I just need some air. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.14,0:51:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.35,0:51:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey.\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.72,0:51:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,See you tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.23,0:51:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.25,0:52:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.41,0:52:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-Gloria.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.79,0:52:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.84,0:52:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and see if Dede and the kids\Nare still eating dinner, would ya, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.30,0:52:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They called an hour ago, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.22,0:52:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids had trains to catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.80,0:52:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, they said to tell you, though,\Nthat they understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.14,0:52:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.97,0:52:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.54,0:52:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that, and I'm sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.25,0:52:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but our staff already went home.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.67,0:52:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back tomorrow,\NI'll make sure that we get you into see…
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.46,0:53:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a problem, Gloria?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.51,0:53:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mr. Donato, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.88,0:53:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we… we had an appointment,\Nbut we hit traffic, so we're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.97,0:53:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.68,0:53:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole staff is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.18,0:53:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, I'll take this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.27,0:53:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-Come on into my office.\N-Not me,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.52,0:53:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.49,0:53:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, uh…
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.20,0:53:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank told me about your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.62,0:53:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,-Nick.\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.62,0:53:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Frank thinks this is a scam.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.04,0:53:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That it's, like, blood money\Nto cover up mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.38,0:53:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, at least, you're open-minded.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.63,0:53:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I just think that the boys might want\Ntheir dad's story told in your report,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.34,0:53:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.72,0:53:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, sure. Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.81,0:53:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you gonna take notes or somethin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.98,0:53:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.86,0:54:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh…
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.27,0:54:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, our stenographer\Nalready went home for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.99,0:54:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.99,0:54:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you type?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.04,0:54:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha-- Uh…
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.42,0:54:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a minute here. There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.71,0:54:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh…
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.47,0:54:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we…
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.88,0:54:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, start with your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.84,0:54:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Karen Donato.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.01,0:54:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband, Nick…
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.02,0:54:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nicholas Donato,\Nwas a New York City firefighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.94,0:54:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladder 179 out of Staten Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.73,0:54:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.20,0:54:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you…
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.58,0:54:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me more about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.29,0:55:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have like a list of questions\Nyou could ask me maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.04,0:55:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, well, actually I… I don't…\NI don't usually do this part myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.76,0:55:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I just… It's harder\Nthan I thought it was gonna be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.26,0:55:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.72,0:55:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, well, if you're uncomfortable--
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.10,0:55:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband of eight years,\Nand I can't even think of anything to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.94,0:55:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, uh, he must have been a good…\Na good dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.78,0:55:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.94,0:55:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh God, he was a great dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.24,0:55:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He would come home every night after work,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.91,0:55:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd throw the ball with Nicky Jr.,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.91,0:55:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he would read Patty a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.08,0:55:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't even mind\Nwhen Tyler made number two.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.50,0:55:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,-He said he liked changing diapers.\N-Well, that's a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.21,0:55:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.22,0:55:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He was my whole world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.77,0:55:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-Can I have a tissue, please?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.56,0:56:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.65,0:56:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.69,0:56:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, everybody\Nkeeps telling me to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.74,0:56:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.41,0:56:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm never gonna get over him.\N-Well, it's still very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.54,0:56:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, never.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.17,0:56:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm really sorry.\N-No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.67,0:56:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all right. Look, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.50,0:56:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want you to know there's\Nno pressure to sign on to the fund today.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.38,0:56:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Your status as a single mother--
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.97,0:56:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not gonna take any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.05,0:56:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Not now, no, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.30,0:56:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there's no money in the world\Nthat's good enough for Nick.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.64,0:56:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,-I didn't mean--\N-You know, I had him in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.10,0:56:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We had so many…
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.77,0:56:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,dreams and plans…
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.03,0:56:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,…and things we were gonna do.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.82,0:56:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he was just gone.\NHe was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.16,0:57:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't even eat breakfast.\NHe was just gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.75,0:57:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're trying to give me money,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.67,0:57:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank wants me to make a stink,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.34,0:57:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there's lawyers calling me\Nand telling me to sue everybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.76,0:57:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the phone just won't stop ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.43,0:57:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's never the phone call I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.26,0:57:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's never the call saying\Nthat they found his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.73,0:57:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That they're gonna bring him home.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.98,0:57:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And no offense,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.06,0:57:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want you,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.40,0:57:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I want all of you\Nto please stop calling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.86,0:57:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.03,0:57:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.83,0:57:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I wasted your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.78,0:58:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Kenny?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.20,0:58:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I met a widow today.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.54,0:58:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Three kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.25,0:58:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.79,0:58:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.51,0:58:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know what to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.93,0:58:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, sometimes,\Nthere isn't anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.99,0:59:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,-That one's blocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.95,0:59:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's hard to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.70,0:59:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll… I'll call when I get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.37,0:59:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,People are collapsing from the smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.04,0:59:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye. Bye-bye. Bye. Sorry. Sorr--
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.88,0:59:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hi, hon.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.26,0:59:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,By now I guess you've heard about\Nthe mess in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.51,0:59:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-Um…
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.93,0:59:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a plane just hit here, too,\Non the western side of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.21,0:59:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not\Nthe preferred option
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.17,1:00:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the president of the United States,\Nor any member of this body.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.80,1:00:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the last option.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.34,1:00:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can make the case
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.06,1:00:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is obvious\Nthat Saddam Hussein continues
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.77,1:00:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this buildup of weapons\Nof mass destruction,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.06,1:00:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and his desire and effort even in…
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.73,1:00:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to and including nuclear weapons.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.36,1:00:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But we are not the ones\Nwho are forcing this issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.57,1:00:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The president and his resolution\Ndid not force the issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.45,1:00:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It is Saddam Hussein\Nwho is forcing this issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.37,1:00:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will…
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.66,1:00:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Final stop\Non this express train,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.58,1:00:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,New York Penn Station.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.08,1:00:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Next stop, New York Penn Station.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.82,1:01:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I… I think the most\Nimportant thing is that we stand united.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.91,1:01:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the only way\Nthat they're going to respond to you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.50,1:01:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is if they know you're speaking as one.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.79,1:01:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-Excuse me for a moment.\N-Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.80,1:01:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You came. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.80,1:01:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We start in a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.68,1:01:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,An enemy in our midst.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.97,1:01:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,-Ah, hi. Priya Khundi.\N-Yes, I remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.89,1:01:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Mr. Feinberg send you here\Nto spy on us or to listen?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.19,1:01:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,-Actually, he doesn't know I came.\N-Ah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.61,1:01:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's easier for him\Nif we just remain numbers, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.61,1:01:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,More manageable?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.65,1:01:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right, it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.70,1:01:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, I understand. Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.83,1:01:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,-But you came.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.99,1:01:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah, um, I've been following your blog.\N-Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.83,1:01:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wife, Katherine,\Nshe had a job at Kyle and MacAllan.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.50,1:02:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.00,1:02:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That, um, was her dream job.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.59,1:02:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it would have been mine too.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.97,1:02:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I… I was, uh…
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.06,1:02:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna start that week.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.60,1:02:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.52,1:02:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm glad that you…
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.23,1:02:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.28,1:02:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So can I ask you then?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.03,1:02:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What would your life be worth\Non your boss's spreadsheet?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.75,1:02:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not married,\Nso, um, less than Katherine's.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.87,1:02:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you think that's fair?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.42,1:02:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.67,1:02:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But your boss does?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.59,1:02:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't think fair exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.88,1:02:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.51,1:02:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.77,1:02:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But I did come here to listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.40,1:03:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the latest, huh? This is…
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.57,1:03:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sure this is the latest?\NThese totals are accurate?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.20,1:03:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Technically, we rounded up.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.95,1:03:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, it's all right, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.66,1:03:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We're 12 months out.\NThat's an eternity. It's like I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.38,1:03:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,people will wait for a deadline.\NThey're just avoiding it for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.46,1:03:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not avoiding it.\NThey're just avoiding us.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.30,1:03:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.47,1:03:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, yeah.\NFix The Fund. I remember, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.10,1:03:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my pal.\NThis is my buddy from the town hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.56,1:03:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,His web page is receiving more than\Ntwice the visits ours does every day.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.23,1:03:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a mailing list\Nof almost 7,000 names.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.23,1:03:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So does the phone book.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.23,1:03:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to see him.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.98,1:03:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her it was okay to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.57,1:03:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, he's a leader.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.90,1:03:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a gadfly.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.16,1:03:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He's earning people's trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.20,1:03:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Every income level, first responders…\NThat's what we should be doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.33,1:03:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If he says so, all of them will sue.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.54,1:04:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's he asking for?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.04,1:04:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You should ask him yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.44,1:04:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.94,1:04:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Feinberg.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.44,1:04:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry they left you in here\Nwith the music running.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.24,1:04:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh.\N-Uh…
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.57,1:04:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-Soothes the soul.\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.03,1:04:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this was the Lincoln Center cast,\Nif I'm not mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.91,1:04:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Bartoli was otherworldly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.50,1:04:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you're an opera fan.\NI was on the board that year.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.79,1:04:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife, Katherine, she was, uh…
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.30,1:04:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She sang soprano\Nin an amateur touring choir.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.42,1:04:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I sing tenor. That's how we met.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.63,1:04:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she must have had a lovely voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.22,1:04:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.64,1:05:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Would that help her fit into your formula?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.98,1:05:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you read my website?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.56,1:05:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I will confess I don't,\Nbecause I'm not a computer guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.03,1:05:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,-Ah.\N-My staff handles all that,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.32,1:05:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and they tell me\Nyou're a very reasonable man.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.28,1:05:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I understand it,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.53,1:05:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you've taken on somewhat\Nof a leadership role
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.24,1:05:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, amongst the people that we serve.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.58,1:05:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,-Mm-hmm.\N-That's nice. Good. Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.04,1:05:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,-Uh, why don't we talk?\N-That's why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.84,1:05:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.18,1:05:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we could make some adjustments.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.93,1:05:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We could, uh, you know,\Nraise the baselines.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.23,1:05:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So you think this is about the money?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.60,1:05:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, of course, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.31,1:05:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That it's greed?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.57,1:05:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No, no, no, no. Not greed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.24,1:05:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, yes. Greed, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.61,1:05:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Money puts food on people's tables
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.41,1:06:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and it puts roofs over people's heads.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.41,1:06:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing dirty\Nor demeaning about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.83,1:06:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but let's not pretend\Nlike it doesn't matter. It does.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.50,1:06:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps people move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.84,1:06:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.59,1:06:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-What do you mean who?\N-Do you know any of our names?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.05,1:06:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you met any of us yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.14,1:06:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact, I have, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.35,1:06:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.72,1:06:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And what were they worth?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.69,1:06:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.64,1:06:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now…\NNow you're talking about numbers,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.98,1:06:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know, pretending--
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.02,1:06:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.53,1:06:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw what out? Throw what out?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.90,1:06:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,-Throw out your formula.\N-I can't. I can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.66,1:06:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to have something rational.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.82,1:06:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it. I understand. I got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.45,1:06:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But my wife is not a statistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.08,1:06:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, certainly not,\Nbut we do have to go by a set of rules.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.96,1:06:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Will your rules help Graham Morris?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.92,1:06:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Graham Morris. His partner died\Ntwo weeks before their civil ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.76,1:07:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but your fund would give\Nhis full claim to his parents
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.51,1:07:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,who condemned his lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.05,1:07:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-I recall him.\N-They were estranged.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.35,1:07:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely estranged, Mr. Feinberg.\NIs that fair?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.69,1:07:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just the administrators on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.44,1:07:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the section\Nof your rules
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.44,1:07:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that limits injuries\Nto only those that occurred right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.36,1:07:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We have cleanup workers\Nwho come to our meetings.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.49,1:07:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-They have polyps from asbestos.\N-I think the thing--
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.82,1:07:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They were on that site for weeks,\Nfor weeks, breathing in that crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.91,1:07:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hmm.\N-But according to your rules,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.70,1:07:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,unless they got to that site\Nwithin three days of the attack--
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.96,1:07:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's because\Nwe have to draw the line somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.13,1:07:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If we award every worker\Nwho was injured on that site,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.25,1:07:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, where does it end? You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.80,1:07:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, you tell me.\NThat's up to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.30,1:07:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The law gives you broad discretion\Nas special master, does it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.97,1:07:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yes, it does.\N-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.81,1:07:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And responsibilities.\NResponsibilities to the taxpayers,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.65,1:07:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to objectivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.06,1:07:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I… I can't bend the rules\Nfor every case that doesn't fit the mold.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.44,1:07:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.36,1:08:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Congress did.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.20,1:08:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You know they did.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.16,1:08:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When the law said that we could sue\Ntwo airlines out of business,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.83,1:08:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Congress rewrote that law like that,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.08,1:08:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in a day.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.54,1:08:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.92,1:08:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the big corporations\Nasked them to.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.13,1:08:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But when 7,000 citizens come to you\Nand they ask you for respect
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.88,1:08:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask not to be treated\Nlike some numbers on a spreadsheet,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.97,1:08:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you act like that law\Ncame down from Sinai.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.02,1:08:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Mr. Feinberg, don't. Don't. Don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.94,1:08:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me\Nyou can't give us what we want.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.40,1:08:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just tell us\Nthat we are not the top priority.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.48,1:08:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Admit that,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.44,1:08:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.24,1:08:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.50,1:08:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hello?\N-Is this Kenneth Feinberg?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.88,1:09:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,-Come here. Come here. Goddamn it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.88,1:09:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hello?\N-Yeah, hi. Is this Kenneth Feinberg?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.55,1:09:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Who's this?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.93,1:09:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Bart Cuthbert, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.43,1:09:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, we haven't met.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.89,1:09:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I represent a claimant to your fund.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.31,1:09:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, this is a private line.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.77,1:09:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Fund matters should go through my office.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.86,1:09:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, the office, yes.\NI spoke to someone at the office
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.65,1:09:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,who said you took the meeting\Non this case yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.74,1:09:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, it's a young woman\Nby the name of Karen Donato.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.45,1:09:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Widow of Nicholas?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.45,1:09:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we spoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.08,1:09:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a fireman with three sons\Naged, um, eight, six, and four.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.33,1:09:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-Look--\N-What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.21,1:09:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's an unusual scenario,\Nyou see.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.50,1:09:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I don't mean\Nto cause you any trouble, Mr. Feinberg.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.46,1:09:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken. Ken. No, go ahead. I'm used to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.88,1:09:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Well, Ken,\Nyou see, my client, Melanie Vale,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.26,1:09:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,was Mr. Donato's mistress.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.14,1:09:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm not… I'm not sure I heard correctly.\N-You heard correctly.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.85,1:09:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Melanie Vale and Nick Donato\Nhave two daughters of their own
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.94,1:10:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,ages one and three\Nat the time of the attack.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.07,1:10:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I have DNA results to prove paternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.65,1:10:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My secretary\Ncan fax them over to your office.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.99,1:10:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Feinberg?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.74,1:10:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.37,1:10:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, all right. Well, I'm looking forward\Nto going over the papers.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.75,1:10:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said,\NI'm not trying to make trouble here.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.04,1:10:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want you to know that when\Nyou cut that check for Mr. Donato's life,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.51,1:10:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it needs to go to five children\Ninstead of three.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.09,1:10:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to hearing from you soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.75,1:10:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.76,1:11:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So your office said that you had, uh,\Nsome more questions about Nick.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.26,1:11:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Really it's more\Njust of a… a record-keeping thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.51,1:11:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you we don't want the money.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.35,1:11:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,-Of course. Yeah.\N-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.23,1:11:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh… Oh, look.\NThere's your wedding pictures.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.94,1:11:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No…
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.65,1:11:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, this is just for show.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.44,1:11:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,-The real one was at City Hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.53,1:11:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I was, you know,\Nas big as a circus tent.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.86,1:11:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I… I told him that I didn't need\Nanything all grand and fancy
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.99,1:11:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,just to prove that he loved me, but, uh…
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.00,1:11:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, he worked doubles\Nfor a whole year.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.29,1:11:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't take a nickel\Nfrom my family or anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.96,1:11:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just so we could have\Nthat picture on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.30,1:11:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He was like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.64,1:11:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And that, I'm assuming, Nicky Jr. there?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.02,1:11:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.31,1:12:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, that was a girl.\NWe lost her. She was a preemie.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.32,1:12:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh, I'm sorry.\N-That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.86,1:12:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Eden.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.45,1:12:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Most dads don't want little girls,\Nbut Nicky always did.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.95,1:12:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.83,1:12:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't need to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.87,1:12:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.16,1:12:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't have to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.37,1:12:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,-I got cereal for the kids.\N-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.71,1:12:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.75,1:12:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'll be right back. Sorry.\N-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.51,1:12:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.55,1:12:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.26,1:12:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,discuss Nick's claim.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.97,1:12:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I already told you, we're not making one.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.31,1:12:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know, of course, but I just…
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.52,1:12:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, just in case Karen decides to…
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.35,1:12:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, let me… Can I show you something?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.94,1:12:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This… I wanna show this number here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.99,1:12:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just, uh…
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.82,1:12:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a presumptive calculation.\NThat means…
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.33,1:12:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what it means to presume.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.17,1:13:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You and Nick were… were very close.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.30,1:13:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.63,1:13:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He was my kid brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.05,1:13:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So I… I have to assume
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.10,1:13:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you would know
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.68,1:13:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,if there was something that Nick
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.69,1:13:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't necessarily want Karen to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.78,1:13:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother was a family man.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.78,1:13:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. Of course, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.87,1:13:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not signing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.74,1:13:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank, this is money for those boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.75,1:13:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's tax-free.\NIt's not every day the government--
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.75,1:13:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nicky died 'cause of people like you\Nholding the purse strings.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.92,1:13:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you think you could come here\Nand make it right
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.17,1:13:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,by tossing money on his grave?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.26,1:13:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of his house.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.43,1:14:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.88,1:14:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,See, this is Tom Jr.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.71,1:14:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think he looks older?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.13,1:14:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom Jr.'s the one not in uniform.\NHe was a civilian contractor.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.72,1:14:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,His brother, Dave,\Nrejoined to fight for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.72,1:14:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very brave.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.10,1:14:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They were only 11 months apart.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.60,1:14:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Like two peas in a pod growing up.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.15,1:14:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a chance to meet Tom's partner,\NGraham Morris.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.23,1:14:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-The gold digger?\N-Tom.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.24,1:14:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What my husband means to say\Nis that man is a liar.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.57,1:15:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He and Tom were living together.\NHe said that they had plans to--
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.37,1:15:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They were roommates.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.21,1:15:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom had girlfriends. He would…
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.58,1:15:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-Mrs…?\N-Biros.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.13,1:15:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Biros, this boy had a long history
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.21,1:15:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of being infatuated with our son.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.22,1:15:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He tried to get his hooks in him,\Nbut Tom did…
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.43,1:15:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew our son.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.81,1:15:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,These guys just crawl out of the woodwork.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.36,1:15:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure your office sees a lot of those.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.86,1:15:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't get that sense from him.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.40,1:15:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that always the way?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.71,1:15:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Rumor has it\Nthat your numbers are a little stagnant.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.38,1:15:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Still plenty of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.76,1:15:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You had plenty of time,\Nand you've signed what, 900?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.84,1:16:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's… That's not enough, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.47,1:16:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I…
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.31,1:16:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I sat down with your friend, Charles Wolf.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.23,1:16:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,-Wolf? Well, good luck with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.73,1:16:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's fighting for the "left behind,"\Nby the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.73,1:16:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not trying to help\Nthe rich get richer.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.11,1:16:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,See, it's that kind of accusation\Nthat has people calling you insensitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.82,1:16:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.24,1:16:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I emphasized our common ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.87,1:16:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A rising tide lifts all boats.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.12,1:16:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I think\NI'm mixing a metaphor.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.29,1:16:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But the point is,\Nif his supporters join our cause,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.67,1:16:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we have enough participants\Nto certify a suit.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.13,1:16:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.59,1:16:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you threatening a class action?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.97,1:16:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm offering to help you out here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.47,1:16:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.43,1:16:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can afford to roll the dice,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.97,1:16:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to win or lose a case\Nover the course of 15 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.56,1:16:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of those people cannot.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.31,1:16:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, with all due respect, you haven't\Nmet these people, your staff has.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.15,1:16:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got news for ya.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.48,1:16:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They hate your guts.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.11,1:17:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe they do, maybe they don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.20,1:17:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm offering them is a choice,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.36,1:17:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm here as a friend\Nto give you the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.58,1:17:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise the ceiling on the top awards,\Nand I'll deliver everybody to your fund.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.00,1:17:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrapped in a bow.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.79,1:17:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's win this together, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.13,1:17:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't the latest number,\Nis it, Ken?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.88,1:17:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen percent?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.68,1:17:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,John, we still have four months\Ntill the statutory deadline,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.18,1:17:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm… I'm confident.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.77,1:17:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.48,1:17:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Confident.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.06,1:17:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Companies are getting nervous, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.90,1:17:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,John, I didn't know we were, uh,\Nhaving a meeting with the airline lobby.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.65,1:17:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just here to listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.16,1:17:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We're told Lee Quinn\Nis planning to bring suit
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.49,1:17:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you give more money at the top.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.95,1:17:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Quinn is not the issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.37,1:17:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You really want to change the law\Nto help people?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.92,1:17:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There are plenty\Nof emergency workers and firemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.75,1:18:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They inhaled toxic chemicals.\NDidn't get sick till months later.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.96,1:18:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,-This law doesn't cover them.\N-No.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.26,1:18:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be unproductive.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.59,1:18:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If you change rules, this gets kicked\Nback to the Congress for a comment period.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.81,1:18:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,-Have you experienced a comment period?\N-No.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.73,1:18:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be on their soapboxes ten months\Nafter the whole statute's kaput.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.19,1:18:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole economy is in the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.15,1:18:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody gets anything,\Nincluding re-elected.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.36,1:18:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yeah…
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.36,1:18:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.78,1:18:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Quinn only cares about\Nthe people at the top
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.03,1:18:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,'cause that's where he gets his paycheck.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.20,1:18:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-His lawsuit is a problem for us.\N-Look, I work for the taxpayers.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.41,1:18:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We pay our share of taxes too.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.04,1:18:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but you don't have to look\Nthe victims in the eye.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.63,1:18:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As the special master,\Nyou have broad discretionary power,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.67,1:18:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,even within your formula.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.05,1:18:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All we're asking is you use it here\Nto make Quinn happy so he goes away.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.01,1:18:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said Ken, neutral party.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.14,1:18:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You have DOJ's support,\Nwhatever you decide.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.79,1:20:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Feinberg?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.58,1:20:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-I thought I might see you here.\N-Uh…
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.92,1:20:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hello, Mr. Wolf.\N-Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.17,1:20:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Katherine would have appreciated\Nthis modern stuff, but I don't…
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.01,1:20:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I… I can't understand music\Nthat you have to,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.64,1:20:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, struggle to listen to.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.72,1:21:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.35,1:21:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I… I do. Well, Puccini, it ain't.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.27,1:21:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We can agree on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.77,1:21:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought\Nyou'd be in the seat of honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.20,1:21:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.16,1:21:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-That bad, huh?\N-Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.87,1:21:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, um…
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.12,1:21:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason I even wanted to do this,\Nwas I really believed
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.08,1:21:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I should serve my country\Nin its time of need. I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.38,1:21:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe part of that's ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.55,1:21:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but… here we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.30,1:21:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got, what, 1100 families on board
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.97,1:21:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and 6,000 more to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.52,1:21:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. Yeah, well…
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.19,1:21:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want you to know\Nthat I know the fund's not perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.94,1:21:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people who just don't fit\Nwithin the rules that we wrote.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.49,1:21:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.20,1:22:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I honestly don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.37,1:22:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.34,1:22:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that you're not the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.92,1:22:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.09,1:22:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a fortune cookie.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.05,1:22:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Katherine and I,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.76,1:22:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this town that we lived in years ago\Nin Upstate New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.85,1:22:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,-Uh, Ithaca, you know.\N-Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.77,1:22:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There was\Nthis gorgeous bridge.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.06,1:22:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Depression-era. Beautiful.\NTo me? Beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.98,1:22:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And developers wanted to knock it down
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.61,1:22:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,'cause they were gonna\Nput in an interstate.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.07,1:22:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So I got on the city council,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.32,1:22:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and I spent two years,\Nand all of our savings,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.79,1:22:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,fighting for that hunk of concrete.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.87,1:22:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they demolished it,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.29,1:22:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I sat around the house\Nmoping for a couple of weeks,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.71,1:22:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling sorry for myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.34,1:22:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Katherine,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.97,1:23:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, she looked at me one day,\Nand she told me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.43,1:23:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"You're not the bridge." Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.98,1:23:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It is rubble,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.65,1:23:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.82,1:23:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I am still here.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.82,1:23:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.90,1:23:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Fighting a new lost cause, but you know…
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.36,1:23:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-Which is me, I suppose.\N-No. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.95,1:23:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's… See, I have\Nnothing against you, Mr. Feinberg.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.66,1:23:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,-Look--\N-I wanna make that clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.04,1:23:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-Okay.\N-Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.96,1:23:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I just… Look, I may have screwed\Nthis whole thing up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.00,1:23:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Very possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.29,1:23:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I try to fix it now,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.38,1:23:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,if I even go on record\Nsaying this thing even needs fixing,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.47,1:23:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,trust me, courts are gonna throw it back\Nto Congress and they'll let it die.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.18,1:23:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing for anyone, just dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.31,1:23:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-Then it deserves to be.\N-Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.14,1:23:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-Because it's not perfect?\N-No. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.60,1:23:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not just.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.07,1:23:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't change that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.48,1:23:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, something has to change.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.61,1:23:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Find it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.94,1:25:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Call off the search party.\NI found him.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.78,1:25:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you sleep here?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.99,1:25:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.99,1:25:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going through these cases,\Nthe uncommitted ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.79,1:25:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on with that, uh…\Nthe civil union suit you're working on?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.38,1:25:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, that's one of dozens.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.42,1:25:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be an issue\Nfor New York residents
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.71,1:25:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,'cause Pataki just extended\Nthe spousal benefits
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.38,1:25:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,for gay people whose partners died.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.93,1:25:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Virginia legislature feels differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.06,1:25:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we gotta\Ncall the governor, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.60,1:25:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, obviously we can't help everyone\Nwith special interests.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.06,1:26:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have to set limits,\Nbut it's a start.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.53,1:26:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's the civil union, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.82,1:26:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of these poor people,\Nthese first responders, this is trickier.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.66,1:26:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't know\Nthey were sick for months.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.53,1:26:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-Look at these. This is…\N-Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.16,1:26:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NWe're gonna have to take the heat on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.41,1:26:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna have to set the formula aside.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.00,1:26:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,-Ken--\N-I know. I know. I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.04,1:26:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. We're in the weeds here.\NThat's where we should be.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.88,1:26:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do this, we have to go\Nthe whole way. Can't go halfway.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.63,1:26:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to consider\Nevery claimant individually.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.09,1:26:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If they can't come here to see us,\Nwe'll have to go and see them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.39,1:26:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand? Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.06,1:26:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.02,1:26:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.44,1:26:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.85,1:26:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, set some meetings.\NI'm gonna get coffee.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.07,1:26:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and a few of the other stronger guys,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.95,1:26:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we pried open the doors\Nso that everyone could… could get away.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.50,1:26:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's… that's when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.13,1:27:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, the oxygen ignited all the fuel and…
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.47,1:27:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that was it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.35,1:27:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Guy like me thinks he's tough.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.64,1:27:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinks he can handle anything\Nthat's thrown at him.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.52,1:27:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's until you look in the eyes\Nof a five-year-old and a six-year-old,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.86,1:27:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and you tell 'em that, uh…
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.36,1:27:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've been lying to 'em,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.70,1:27:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and that, uh, Mommy's not coming home.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.45,1:27:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,…and asked me if he was wearing\Nhis wedding ring, and I said, "No. Why?"
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.58,1:27:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You need something?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.54,1:27:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I thought I'd join in, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.25,1:27:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,just perhaps listen, but--
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.71,1:27:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sandra, is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.18,1:27:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on. Whenever you're ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.43,1:28:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to ask each time he flew\Nfor school or work,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.27,1:28:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I would ask for his itinerary.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.11,1:28:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Just so I could breathe a little easier
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.74,1:28:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing he landed…
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.12,1:28:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,back on solid ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.88,1:28:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes a parent to know that feeling…
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.80,1:28:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll never have it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.47,1:28:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fishing fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.39,1:28:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He made them…
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.85,1:28:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We made them together.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.06,1:28:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife and I want you to keep it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.78,1:28:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.78,1:28:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.66,1:28:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We were told, uh, because he\Nsuffered about 90% burns over his body,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.12,1:29:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,he might not appear\Nto be the same person we know him to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.59,1:29:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we got a call\Nfrom the medical examiner's office
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.63,1:29:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,saying that there was a mix-up
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.51,1:29:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had to make another identification.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.10,1:29:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It turned out we spent four days
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.39,1:29:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bedside of a stranger…
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.19,1:29:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,…while Alex…
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.57,1:29:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,While he died.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.99,1:29:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nmy wife and I, we were thinking,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.53,1:29:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"Gosh, those poor people."
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.33,1:29:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at first, you assume\Nit's… it's happening to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.75,1:29:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then within a few hours,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.96,1:29:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they, of course, confirmed\Nthat she was there for a meeting.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.96,1:29:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We realized we were one of those people.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.67,1:29:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it… it was staggering.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.26,1:29:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.51,1:30:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the 85th floor.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.97,1:30:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We actually started\Ngoing down the stairs early.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.35,1:30:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can call me Jean.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.89,1:30:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean, tell me more about your son.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.36,1:30:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, when did he move away from Iowa?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.69,1:30:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1997.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.28,1:30:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He got a job as an analyst right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.86,1:30:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He was actually so excited.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.57,1:30:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.57,1:30:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think you should take\Nwhat the government's giving.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.99,1:30:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-I got bad anxiety.\N-Jerry.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.91,1:30:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't sleep much at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.16,1:30:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah, I can't imagine.\N-I had to move out of the city.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.67,1:30:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't bear seeing\Nthe hole in the skyline.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.63,1:30:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do everything I can\Nto expedite this process.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.97,1:30:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-Well, Florida's nice.\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.34,1:30:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"It seems as if I don't feel anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.10,1:30:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but inside I do."
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.97,1:30:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"Inside, I wanna burst\Nand just talk to everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.06,1:30:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,about what I'm holding in."
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.02,1:30:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"I wanna say how much pain I have,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.90,1:30:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wanna say\Nall the pressure that I have."
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.32,1:31:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have to control myself emotionally."
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.58,1:31:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have to help with them\Nand be strong for them,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.58,1:31:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but also still be strong for me."
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.50,1:31:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"My dad was good at that."
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.33,1:31:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have to be the man that he was."
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.98,1:31:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.11,1:31:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So we keep going,\Nright up to the deadline.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.53,1:31:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we get the word out wider,\Nmake a public statement.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.20,1:31:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.32,1:31:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you announce this publicly,\Nit starts to look like
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.78,1:31:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a change in policy,\Nthen the law goes back to Congress…
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.08,1:31:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What if\Nsomeone else announces it?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.04,1:31:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're meeting with people.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.84,1:31:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.59,1:32:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I hear you've been telling them\Nthat you're throwing out the formula.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.68,1:32:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope. The law gives me discretion,\Nwhich someone reminded me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.39,1:32:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to use it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.81,1:32:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But I promise you, if people come aboard,\NI will do everything I can to help them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.86,1:32:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Guaranteed by what, your word?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.70,1:32:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Charles. I… I mean…
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.49,1:32:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.87,1:32:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.28,1:32:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Feinberg,\Nyou've been telling us for two years
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.08,1:32:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're nothing but a numbers cruncher\Nfor the government,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.79,1:32:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you're asking us to trust you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.21,1:32:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm asking you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.38,1:32:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You already have their trust,\Nand you earned it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.43,1:32:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Help them trust me too.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.76,1:32:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you just trying to win?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.52,1:32:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm trying to make things right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.99,1:33:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When's your deposition with Lee Quinn?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.28,1:33:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Monday.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.28,1:33:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He's gonna tell you you wanted kids.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.50,1:33:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty-year-old married female\Nwho was pregnant,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.92,1:33:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or even she's just trying to get pregnant,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.21,1:33:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the damage settlement shoots way up.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.50,1:33:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Way up. Skyward.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.30,1:33:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And Quinn's gonna coach you\Nthrough every step.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.88,1:33:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When to cry, when to quiver your lip.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.56,1:33:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know this?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.93,1:33:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause we're the same guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.27,1:33:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'd do.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.50,1:34:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashcroft stood you up?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.09,1:34:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, he's under pressure of his own.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.64,1:34:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think it's a message?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.72,1:34:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Give Quinn what he wants?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.35,1:34:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not suggesting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.77,1:34:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still time. You always say\Nthey'll come in at the deadline.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.65,1:34:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I'm wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.24,1:34:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I'm wrong, Camille?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.45,1:34:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.79,1:34:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You did everything you could.\NEveryone did everything they could.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.33,1:34:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,-A call for you, Ken. Lawyer from Queens.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.92,1:34:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Name's Cuthbert.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.17,1:34:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a message, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.51,1:34:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He already left you three.\NIt's about the Donato case.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.42,1:34:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He says\Nif you don't tell the widow, he will,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.47,1:34:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell you that you have until tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.69,1:34:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.19,1:35:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Grab my bag out of the trunk,\Nplease.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.53,1:35:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, guys. It's time to come in.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.82,1:35:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Karen isn't home yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.07,1:35:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,She told me you called.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.12,1:35:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Said you wouldn't tell her why.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.24,1:35:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When will she be back?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.50,1:35:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Put away your checkbook.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.25,1:35:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're joining the lawsuit.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.63,1:35:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you'll… you'll do whatever\Nyou have to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.96,1:35:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But you know better, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.30,1:35:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I… I would not presume or judge.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.51,1:35:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.01,1:35:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You see her being loyal to a dead guy,\Nyou can't imagine why.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.72,1:35:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank, the signing deadline is Saturday,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.52,1:35:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and after that you won't see me anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.07,1:35:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first thing you said\NI'm glad to hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.03,1:35:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still gonna\Nhave to talk to Karen first.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.03,1:35:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, like I said, she's not home.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.70,1:35:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, I'll pass it along.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.33,1:35:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you would, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.16,1:35:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I think you already know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.17,1:36:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to protect him anymore.\NNick's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.59,1:36:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't know Nick. He was a good man.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.51,1:36:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not about Nick.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.73,1:36:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He went back in for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.69,1:36:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Into the tower.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.73,1:36:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,-Did you know that?\N-No.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.36,1:36:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For all I know,\Nhe heard the evac orders on his radio,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.15,1:36:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and he said,\N"Fuck it, my brother's in there."
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.49,1:36:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He died trying to save me,\Nand you think I should…
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.07,1:36:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I should forget about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.16,1:36:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you have a family?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.12,1:36:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you died tomorrow, what's the worst\Nthey'd find out about you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.12,1:36:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-Maybe you're not such a hero either.\N-I'm not a hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.96,1:36:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, Nick was.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.75,1:36:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nick was.\NHe was a family man. He was a good man.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.42,1:36:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why\Nhe'd want his children taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.30,1:36:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.84,1:36:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank, if I were you,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.64,1:36:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,honestly,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.77,1:37:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what I would do.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.31,1:37:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.94,1:37:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I might… I might wanna sue the hell\Nout of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.48,1:37:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're not the only ones left behind.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.78,1:37:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.32,1:37:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That family wants the money\Nso they can just move on,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.74,1:37:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think they deserve it,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.70,1:37:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think Nick would think so too.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.29,1:37:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm…
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.38,1:37:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna count them\Nas equal beneficiaries.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.92,1:37:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought Karen should know,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.76,1:37:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wanted to tell her myself
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.22,1:37:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so she didn't have to read it\Nin the public record.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.84,1:37:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What are their names?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.05,1:37:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-Karen, go back in the house.\N-No.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.85,1:37:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna know.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.98,1:37:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Jenna and Belle.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.99,1:37:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He always wanted girls.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.96,1:38:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-You happy?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.17,1:38:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mail's here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.55,1:38:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-Do y'all wanna sign for these together?\N-I'll sign.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.64,1:39:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What's it look like there?\NHow many we got?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.85,1:39:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-How many do you have?\N-Thirty. Maybe 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.73,1:39:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.30,1:39:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.01,1:39:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You did the best you could.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.68,1:39:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.51,1:39:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.23,1:39:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You just ask the question?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.28,1:39:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Five.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.53,1:40:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, three, four, five.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.16,1:40:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're working too hard, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.12,1:40:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-Get yourself a drink.\N-No, I'm… I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.58,1:40:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just get on with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.58,1:40:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think I don't respect it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.84,1:40:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Your whole crusade.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.34,1:41:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-That's not what this is.\N-No, I know. I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.39,1:41:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Robin Hood.\NYou're solving everybody's problem
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.60,1:41:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,one good deed at a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.85,1:41:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You poisoned the well.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.10,1:41:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You did, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.77,1:41:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You poisoned the well.\NYou played on people's fear
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.32,1:41:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and their pain and their anger,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:18.57,1:41:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,their distrust of government,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.49,1:41:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to act against their own best interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.91,1:41:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, my girl's birthday is today.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.03,1:41:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Caterer's coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.74,1:41:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,-You gonna meet these numbers or what?\N-Give me a pen.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.88,1:41:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I know, I know it hurts,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.17,1:41:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but fair is not the goal.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.84,1:41:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finish and move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.47,1:41:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.77,1:41:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.31,1:41:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you probably did.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.77,1:41:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You've always been my hero, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.94,1:42:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched you argue\Nin front of Fuld, 1984.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.86,1:42:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You had hair then.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.03,1:42:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Doubt you believed a word you said,\Nbut, man, did it sound good.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.70,1:42:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-What are you doing? Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.50,1:42:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.08,1:42:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.79,1:42:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.67,1:42:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Change your high, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.63,1:42:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.84,1:42:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.60,1:43:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.02,1:43:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-What is going on here?\N-The families.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.32,1:43:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been like this all morning.\NSome calls, some walk-ins.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.94,1:43:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly everyone\Nwants to have a private meeting.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.07,1:43:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.45,1:43:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"By now, many of us have sat down\Nwith Mr. Feinberg, looked him in the eye."
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.66,1:43:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"We've told him\Nit's not the money that we're after."
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.37,1:43:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's for our own government, this system,\Nto treat us all with dignity, respect."
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.71,1:43:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, I can't speak for the system,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.80,1:43:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but I have come to believe\Nin Mr. Feinberg."
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.22,1:43:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's why I'm happy to announce\Nthe fund is fixed."
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.56,1:43:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We just passed 65%.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.06,1:43:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.52,1:44:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,-All right, let's keep going, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.19,1:44:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,-We're really doing it.\N-Well done, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.65,1:44:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.11,1:44:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,-I need your number right there.\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.32,1:44:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be able\Nto bring that by before00?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.36,1:44:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.07,1:44:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that Richmond?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.16,1:44:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-I need that as soon as you're done.\N-Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.95,1:44:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I know your kids start school soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.62,1:44:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you would like,\Nwe can fax a redirect payment
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.54,1:44:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,right into the tuition account,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.92,1:44:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and, uh, that would be helpful.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.92,1:44:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.51,1:44:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What… What I can do is, um,\Nis fax the materials to a copy center.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.05,1:44:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you near one of those?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.51,1:44:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, you know what?\NI can look that up for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.14,1:44:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're… You're still\Nat the Arthur Ave. address?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.82,1:44:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.65,1:44:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.32,1:44:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I should get back to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.41,1:44:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,-Nice to see you.\N-You too.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.04,1:44:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.62,1:45:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still a typo on page three.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.33,1:45:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get right on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.75,1:45:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, you were wrong about Lee Quinn.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.92,1:45:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't try to coach you?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.17,1:45:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He did,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.59,1:45:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're nothing like him.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.85,1:45:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Mr. Feinberg.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.52,1:45:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.62,1:45:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Mrs. Benson.\NI've been, uh, handling your claim myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.70,1:45:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I know there's been an issue\Nwith your husband's life insurance offset.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.37,1:45:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And look, I've been fiddling\Nwith the numbers,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.59,1:45:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and, uh, I want to propose something.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.67,1:45:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you're gonna like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.76,1:45:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We just wanna make sure\Nyou have everything together.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.43,1:45:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This looks good to me.\NYou filled it out well.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.72,1:45:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys wanna give me a hand here?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.77,1:46:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot more\Ndown in the truck.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.27,1:46:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tally it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.48,1:46:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.94,1:46:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NCome on, guys, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.61,1:46:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.57,1:46:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what have you got?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.41,1:46:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A little over 95% so far.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.00,1:46:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we call the president?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.58,1:46:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.33,1:46:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-Let's get drunk with the president.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.67,1:46:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.86,1:47:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Morris, this is Camille Biros\Nfrom the Victim Compensation Fund.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.08,1:47:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you've heard the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.04,1:47:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know\Nbecause of your case,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.92,1:47:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we were able to accommodate\Na great number of people
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.30,1:47:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in similar relationships in New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.64,1:47:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But, um…
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.06,1:47:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.35,1:47:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom's parents being how they are,\Nand Virginia state law,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.82,1:47:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we were not able to accommodate yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.03,1:47:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.87,1:47:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that doesn't help.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.93,1:48:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.22,1:48:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Uh, you know, I just…
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.72,1:48:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna talk to him real quick.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.94,1:48:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mr. Feinberg. I, uh…
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.56,1:48:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-Look, I'm sorry.\N-Come on. Come on over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.36,1:48:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I, um…
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.70,1:48:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I just…
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.04,1:48:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't wanna know.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.20,1:48:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.04,1:48:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.96,1:48:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd get a call after dinner,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.63,1:48:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and he would say it was Frank,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.88,1:48:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, and there was, like,\Na three-alarm in the city or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.47,1:48:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd kiss me goodbye,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.01,1:48:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would pretend like\NI didn't know that he was lying.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.02,1:48:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Then later, I'd be over with Irene,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.73,1:48:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and Frank would come home\Nafter drinking with the boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.61,1:48:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would say,\N"How'd that three-alarm go?"
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.44,1:48:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, he would look at me
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.11,1:49:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with the straightest face you've ever seen\Nin your life, and he'd say,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.53,1:49:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"Nicky's mopping up,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.16,1:49:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but he was a real hero tonight."
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.83,1:49:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"You should've seen him."
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.17,1:49:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"Might be a while though,\Nso don't wait up."
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.05,1:49:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know,\NI don't… I don't hate Frank for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.84,1:49:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Nicky was his little brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.31,1:49:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want him to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.06,1:49:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, of course not.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.43,1:49:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But I used to wish\Nall sorts of things about her.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.27,1:49:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't do anything wrong, Karen.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.07,1:49:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, God tests us.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.44,1:49:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.58,1:49:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you make sure\Nthat they get what they need?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.92,1:49:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,His little girls?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.42,1:50:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.
